<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-085-263 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 083 757</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  August 5 1991 n432 p94(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Medic grows with full-service approach: VAR profits fromhealth-care training. (value-added reseller Medic Computer SystemsandM;)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Grace, Tim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Value-added reseller Medic Computer Systems, a vertical-marketreseller of IBM and Texas Instruments Inc computers specializingin the health care industry, relies heavily on intensive trainingand support services to increase its profitability.andP;  Medic earned$41 million in 1990.andP;  Company officials note that training isespecially important in the health-care industry because of highemployee turnover in medical offices; computer systems in manypractices go unused or under-used and are eventually replaced withsystems from another VAR because the first reseller did notprovide enough support.andP;  Medic offers 17 classes at its 20regional sales and support centers for both new users and thoseadding new software modules to existing systems.andP;  Other servicesthe company provides include periodic on-site visits and a yearlyusers' conference.andP;  The company says that repeat business accountsfor 80 percent of its sales and that 70 percent of new sales arethe result of referrals from established clients and industryconsultants.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Medic Computer Systems (Services).andO;Topic:     Value-added resellersCase StudyVertical MarketHealth CareUser Training.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>